  "text": "Grafana datasource plugin queries flow through a sophisticated architecture:\n\n**HTTP API Entry Point**: The POST /ds/query endpoint is handled by QueryMetricsV2 (pkg/api/ds_query.go) which receives the MetricRequest and invokes the queryDataService.QueryData method, returning responses via toJsonStreamingResponse and response.JSONStreaming (pkg/api/response/response.go).\n\n**Query Service Orchestration**: The ServiceImpl in pkg/services/query/query.go implements the main query flow:\n- QueryData and QueryDataNew methods parse the metric request, handle expressions via expressionService.TransformData (pkg/expr/transform.go), and route to either handleExpressions for expression queries or handleQuerySingleDatasource for plugin-backed datasources\n- handleQuerySingleDatasource builds a backend.QueryDataRequest and routes through either the legacy plugin client flow or the modern query-service datasource client flow using ConvertBackendRequestToDataRequest (pkg/expr/query_convert.go)\n\n**Plugin Client**: The plugins.Client service (pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go::Service.QueryData) wraps the plugin execution, calling the underlying plugin implementation and post-processing response frames to set RefID values.\n\n**gRPC Plugin Communication**: The ClientV2 (pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go) handles gRPC communication with backend plugins:\n- Converts backend.QueryDataRequest to protobuf using backend.ToProto().QueryDataRequest\n- Calls c.DataClient.QueryData via gRPC\n- Converts the protobuf response back to backend.QueryDataResponse using backend.FromProto().QueryDataResponse, deserializing data frames\n\n**Aggregator API Server**: The plugin handler infrastructure in pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/handler.go registers HTTP routes that proxy to plugin backends through PluginHandler.registerRoutes. The QueryServiceType route invokes QueryDataHandler (pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go) which:\n- Decodes the incoming QueryDataRequest\n- Validates datasource UID and type\n- Obtains plugin context via PluginContextProvider\n- Calls h.client.QueryData (the plugin backend)\n- Wraps the response in aggregationv0alpha1.QueryDataResponse\n\n**Response Serialization**: The Responder (pkg/aggregator/apiserver/util/responder.go) uses responsewriters.WriteRawJSON to serialize the QueryDataResponse object. The QueryDataResponse type (pkg/aggregator/apis/aggregation/v0alpha1/types.go) wraps backend.QueryDataResponse, which contains the data frames with metric/time series data.\n\nThe complete chain ensures queries are validated, routed to appropriate datasource plugins (either local gRPC or remote query-service), executed with proper context and authentication, and returned as typed data frames in JSON format for consumption by Grafana dashboards and frontend applications."
}

